issue.title: Adding ROS2 control / protocol
issue.body:
@WestlingPi  wrote:

> I am going to start to implement an alternative protocol for remoteUart for integration with ROS2. I think it is mostly the message format and encoding/decoding of message that is going to be different. I am thinking of introducing a new ifdef for the alternative protocol (similar to the flash code have 2 formats, one for autodetect and another for remoteAdc). [@RoboDurden](https://github.com/RoboDurden) Would that be something that you would be interested in to upstream to your gen2.x repo? I think maybe more people would be interested in a protocol that integrates with a ROS2 driver (https://github.com/WestlingPi/hoverboard-driver)...

Yes, but please add a RemoteROS2.c and RemoteROS2.h !
Simply copy RemoteUart into these new files and change to your protocol

Maybe you can use this PID controller for ROS2: https://github.com/RoboDurden/Hoverboard-Firmware-Hack-Gen2.x/issues/120#issuecomment-3005454189
I am no PID expert at all, but maybe it can also be used for position iOdom control ?

pull_request.title: Bump flask from 3.1.0 to 3.1.1 in /image/python/3.13/context
pull_request.body:
Bumps [flask](https://github.com/pallets/flask) from 3.1.0 to 3.1.1.
Release notes

Sourced from flask's releases.

3.1.1

This is the Flask 3.1.1 fix release, which fixes bugs but does not otherwise change behavior and should not result in breaking changes compared to the latest feature release.

PyPI: https://pypi.org/project/Flask/3.1.1/ Changes: https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/stable/changes/#version-3-1-1 Milestone https://github.com/pallets/flask/milestone/36?closed=1

  • Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS. GHSA-4grg-w6v8-c28g
  • Fix type hint for cli_runner.invoke. #5645
  • flask --help loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands are shown. #5673
  • Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return AsyncIterable. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier for Quart. #5659
Changelog

Sourced from flask's changelog.

Version 3.1.1

Released 2025-05-13

  • Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS. :ghsa:4grg-w6v8-c28g
  • Fix type hint for cli_runner.invoke. :issue:5645
  • flask --help loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands are shown. :issue:5673
  • Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return AsyncIterable. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier for Quart. :pr:5659
Commits
  • 7fff56f release version 3.1.1
  • 73d6504 Merge commit from fork
  • cbb6c36 update docs about fallback order
  • fb54159 secret key rotation: fix key list ordering
  • 941efd4 use uv (#5727)
  • 0109e49 use uv
  • e785166 Async Iterable Response (#5659)
  • 410e5ab Accept AsyncIterable for responses
  • bfffe87 add ghsa links
  • 73ce26c remove tests about deprecated pkgutil.get_loader (#5702)
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view
